  "text": "Some of the studies we reviewed used indirect laboratory techniques, such as serological tests. Authors working on blood sera collected paired samples to measure the rise in antibodies but did not systematically report the exact timing of the convalescent sample although it influences the sensitivity and specificity of this test [CITATION_1] . Moreover, these techniques tend to be positive during colonization so these results may be less reliable than cultures [CITATION_2] .",
